00:00:14.764 --> 00:00:17.017 position:50% align:center
[NARRATOR] The Student
Council has disbanded,

00:00:17.100 --> 00:00:20.103 position:50% align:center
which means the campaign
season has started anew.

00:00:20.186 --> 00:00:22.105 position:50% align:center
And since the former
council members no longer

00:00:22.188 --> 00:00:25.567 position:50% align:center
have their duties, they don't
have a reason to interact.

00:00:25.650 --> 00:00:27.819 position:50% align:center
Three entire days have passed!

00:00:27.902 --> 00:00:29.279 position:50% align:center
And nothing's happened.

00:00:29.362 --> 00:00:30.113 position:50% align:center
Shock, shock.

00:00:30.196 --> 00:00:32.657 position:50% align:center
Surprise, surprise.

00:00:32.741 --> 00:00:34.826 position:50% align:center
[HAYASAKA] Just woman up
and make the first move.

00:00:34.909 --> 00:00:37.704 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA]
What? That's a terrible idea!

00:00:37.787 --> 00:00:40.331 position:50% align:center
Could you still
be our president?

00:00:40.415 --> 00:00:42.250 position:50% align:center
How could I have been so stupid?

00:00:42.334 --> 00:00:44.878 position:50% align:center
If I talk to him now,
you know what that'd say?

00:00:44.961 --> 00:00:46.379 position:50% align:center
I'm lonely!

00:00:46.463 --> 00:00:48.548 position:50% align:center
Then again, what if
he is equally as lonely

00:00:48.631 --> 00:00:50.550 position:50% align:center
without me as I am without him?

00:00:50.633 --> 00:00:53.011 position:50% align:center
It might even make him
confess his love, right?

00:00:53.094 --> 00:00:54.346 position:50% align:center
[HAYASAKA]
Keep dreaming.

00:00:54.429 --> 00:00:58.433 position:50% align:center
Sick visit, fireworks,
birthday, moon-viewing.

00:00:58.516 --> 00:01:00.310 position:50% align:center
You've had plenty of
chances to make progress,

00:01:00.393 --> 00:01:02.145 position:50% align:center
but nothing to show for it.

00:01:02.228 --> 00:01:03.521 position:50% align:center
Like, seriously.

00:01:03.605 --> 00:01:04.898 position:50% align:center
It's pathetic.

00:01:04.981 --> 00:01:07.067 position:50% align:center
Making a guy fall for you
should not be this hard.

00:01:07.150 --> 00:01:08.193 position:50% align:center
Oh, yeah?

00:01:08.276 --> 00:01:09.819 position:50% align:center
You think you would
have better luck?

00:01:09.903 --> 00:01:11.196 position:50% align:center
Is that it?

00:01:11.279 --> 00:01:12.447 position:50% align:center
Most likely.

00:01:12.530 --> 00:01:15.575 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA grunts]
Then, by all means, woo away!

00:01:15.658 --> 00:01:16.910 position:50% align:center
In fact, why not see if you can

00:01:16.993 --> 00:01:18.828 position:50% align:center
sweep the president
off his feet in one day,

00:01:18.912 --> 00:01:20.080 position:50% align:center
since it's so easy for you!

00:01:20.163 --> 00:01:21.456 position:50% align:center
I never said easy.

00:01:21.539 --> 00:01:22.582 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA]
Everything looks easier

00:01:22.665 --> 00:01:24.000 position:50% align:center
when you're standing
on the sidelines!

00:01:24.084 --> 00:01:25.210 position:50% align:center
[HAYASAKA]
I never said easy.

00:01:25.293 --> 00:01:26.419 position:50% align:center
If you actually tried it,

00:01:26.503 --> 00:01:28.296 position:50% align:center
then you'd know that
the struggle is real!

00:01:28.380 --> 00:01:30.298 position:50% align:center
I never said easy.

00:01:30.382 --> 00:01:32.342 position:50% align:center
Saying that you
can is one thing.

00:01:32.425 --> 00:01:35.345 position:50% align:center
But do you actually have
the skills to back it up?!

00:01:37.806 --> 00:01:41.726 position:50% align:center
If you truly want me
to try my hand at this, I will!

00:01:41.810 --> 00:01:45.397 position:50% align:center
Go right ahead then.
I dare you.

00:03:18.782 --> 00:03:20.742 position:50% align:center
[CLERK 4A]
Have a nice day.

00:03:23.036 --> 00:03:24.412 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI]
Hm?

00:03:26.414 --> 00:03:29.167 position:50% align:center
Hi! Fancy meeting you here!

00:03:29.250 --> 00:03:32.796 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI] Um. Wait, I know you.
You're Shinomiya's maid.

00:03:32.879 --> 00:03:34.422 position:50% align:center
Hayasaka A. Smithee, right?

00:03:34.506 --> 00:03:37.592 position:50% align:center
[gasps] Bingo! You remembered!

00:03:37.676 --> 00:03:39.803 position:50% align:center
That's so sweet!

00:03:41.096 --> 00:03:44.641 position:50% align:center
Well, truth be told, I actually
didn't recognize you at first.

00:03:44.724 --> 00:03:46.434 position:50% align:center
You look a little different.

00:03:46.518 --> 00:03:47.852 position:50% align:center
I'm off the clock!

00:03:47.936 --> 00:03:51.231 position:50% align:center
It's tough acting
formal 24/7, y'know?

00:03:51.314 --> 00:03:53.400 position:50% align:center
Yeah. I bet.

00:03:53.483 --> 00:03:54.984 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA]
She's good.

00:03:55.068 --> 00:03:56.820 position:50% align:center
She waited till he was
in the checkout line,

00:03:56.903 --> 00:03:58.863 position:50% align:center
so he couldn't get away.

00:03:58.947 --> 00:04:00.365 position:50% align:center
Although Hayasaka may, indeed,

00:04:00.448 --> 00:04:02.075 position:50% align:center
have some skill
in this department,

00:04:02.158 --> 00:04:03.410 position:50% align:center
there's absolutely no way

00:04:03.493 --> 00:04:04.953 position:50% align:center
she'll be able to
seduce the president!

00:04:05.036 --> 00:04:06.663 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI]
Your accent has changed, too.

00:04:06.746 --> 00:04:07.789 position:50% align:center
It's less noticeable.

00:04:07.872 --> 00:04:09.624 position:50% align:center
Studying helped with that!

00:04:09.708 --> 00:04:13.086 position:50% align:center
But I know you study your butt
off, too, don't you, Shirogane?

00:04:13.169 --> 00:04:15.213 position:50% align:center
I mean, I try.

00:04:15.296 --> 00:04:16.798 position:50% align:center
[HAYASAKA]
It's embarrassing.

00:04:16.881 --> 00:04:20.093 position:50% align:center
I'm buying a magazine for the
masses right in front of you.

00:04:20.176 --> 00:04:22.262 position:50% align:center
Oh, are you into tech stuff?

00:04:22.345 --> 00:04:25.140 position:50% align:center
Well, I was thinking
about buying a laptop,

00:04:25.223 --> 00:04:26.641 position:50% align:center
but I don't know
which one to get.

00:04:26.725 --> 00:04:28.393 position:50% align:center
Luckily, I ran into you,

00:04:28.476 --> 00:04:30.687 position:50% align:center
and boys know more
about this kind of stuff!

00:04:30.770 --> 00:04:32.564 position:50% align:center
So I'll let you decide!

00:04:32.647 --> 00:04:34.357 position:50% align:center
Computers aren't
really my forte.

00:04:34.441 --> 00:04:35.567 position:50% align:center
[HAYASAKA]
Something tells me your eye

00:04:35.650 --> 00:04:37.110 position:50% align:center
is still better than mine.

00:04:37.193 --> 00:04:40.405 position:50% align:center
Let's stop by the cafeteria
so I can pick your noggin. Cool?

00:04:40.488 --> 00:04:42.115 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA]
She is really good.

00:04:42.198 --> 00:04:43.867 position:50% align:center
[NARRATOR]
The "teach me" strategy.

00:04:43.950 --> 00:04:46.286 position:50% align:center
Instead of demanding
that a child clean his room,

00:04:46.369 --> 00:04:47.912 position:50% align:center
the parent will ask
a question like,

00:04:47.996 --> 00:04:49.247 position:50% align:center
"Where do your toys go?"

00:04:49.330 --> 00:04:51.875 position:50% align:center
and the child will put
them away while explaining.

00:04:51.958 --> 00:04:53.918 position:50% align:center
Humans have an
innate drive to teach,

00:04:54.002 --> 00:04:56.921 position:50% align:center
and Hayasaka has cleverly
used that to her advantage.

00:04:57.005 --> 00:04:58.840 position:50% align:center
Sure. I've got
some time to kill.

00:04:58.923 --> 00:05:00.091 position:50% align:center
Awesome!

00:05:00.175 --> 00:05:04.095 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA]
President!

00:05:06.097 --> 00:05:08.141 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI] Which school
is that uniform from?

00:05:08.224 --> 00:05:10.935 position:50% align:center
[HAYASAKA]
Oh! Firis Girls' Academy.

00:05:11.019 --> 00:05:12.771 position:50% align:center
I'm a second year.

00:05:12.854 --> 00:05:15.732 position:50% align:center
I met the Shinomiyas thanks
to a friend from school.

00:05:15.815 --> 00:05:17.442 position:50% align:center
Now I fill in as
a part-time maid

00:05:17.525 --> 00:05:19.277 position:50% align:center
whenever they're shorthanded.

00:05:19.361 --> 00:05:21.071 position:50% align:center
It's a part-time job?

00:05:21.154 --> 00:05:22.030 position:50% align:center
[HAYASAKA]
Mm-hm.

00:05:22.113 --> 00:05:23.490 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA]
The nerve of this girl,

00:05:23.573 --> 00:05:25.909 position:50% align:center
lying through her teeth with
a straight face like that.

00:05:25.992 --> 00:05:28.036 position:50% align:center
She's a normal student
at Shuchiin Academy,

00:05:28.119 --> 00:05:29.412 position:50% align:center
