00:09:58.264 --> 00:10:01.476 position:50% align:center
You're an outsider
among our peers, Miyuki.

00:10:01.559 --> 00:10:02.977 position:50% align:center
Most students are purebloods

00:10:03.061 --> 00:10:05.647 position:50% align:center
who started Shuchiin
in elementary school.

00:10:05.730 --> 00:10:08.108 position:50% align:center
Right.

00:10:08.191 --> 00:10:10.318 position:50% align:center
Some probably
weren't very thrilled

00:10:10.402 --> 00:10:12.070 position:50% align:center
when they caught wind
of your re-election.

00:10:12.153 --> 00:10:13.488 position:50% align:center
Yeah.

00:10:13.571 --> 00:10:15.365 position:50% align:center
That specific group proved
to be quite the challenge

00:10:15.448 --> 00:10:17.784 position:50% align:center
in my previous
campaign as well.

00:10:17.867 --> 00:10:19.536 position:50% align:center
[CHIKA]
About your speeches.

00:10:19.619 --> 00:10:21.496 position:50% align:center
I think you should
forgo writing them yourself

00:10:21.579 --> 00:10:23.957 position:50% align:center
and put somebody else in charge!

00:10:24.040 --> 00:10:25.500 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI grunts]

00:10:25.583 --> 00:10:27.460 position:50% align:center
[CHIKA] Fortunately, there's
a girl with enough popularity

00:10:27.544 --> 00:10:29.462 position:50% align:center
and charisma to sway the
pureblood's.

00:10:29.546 --> 00:10:32.590 position:50% align:center
And she just happens to
already be in your corner!

00:10:32.674 --> 00:10:33.717 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:10:33.800 --> 00:10:35.135 position:50% align:center
[CHIKA]
Of course...

00:10:35.218 --> 00:10:36.720 position:50% align:center
...I'm talking about--

00:10:36.803 --> 00:10:38.972 position:50% align:center
None other than Shinomiya.

00:10:40.181 --> 00:10:42.726 position:50% align:center
You just officially
lost my vote, Miyuki!

00:10:42.809 --> 00:10:46.396 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI] Wait... Were you
referring to yourself?

00:10:46.479 --> 00:10:48.314 position:50% align:center
If so, my bad.

00:10:49.607 --> 00:10:50.650 position:50% align:center
[STUDENT A]
Have you decided who

00:10:50.734 --> 00:10:51.568 position:50% align:center
you're gonna vote
for in the election?

00:10:51.651 --> 00:10:53.403 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI]
Awkward!

00:10:53.486 --> 00:10:55.780 position:50% align:center
Get your life together and
just walk through the door!

00:10:55.864 --> 00:10:56.614 position:50% align:center
[HAYASAKA]
Hey, President!

00:10:56.698 --> 00:10:57.449 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI shrieks]

00:10:57.532 --> 00:10:59.200 position:50% align:center
How are you?

00:10:59.284 --> 00:11:00.368 position:50% align:center
Oh, wow!

00:11:00.452 --> 00:11:04.914 position:50% align:center
You're here to visit
my class, how lucky!

00:11:04.998 --> 00:11:07.459 position:50% align:center
Have we met somewhere before?

00:11:07.542 --> 00:11:09.169 position:50% align:center
Why, sure we have, silly!

00:11:09.252 --> 00:11:11.129 position:50% align:center
We go to the same
school after all!

00:11:11.212 --> 00:11:14.090 position:50% align:center
[HAYASAKA] So are you here
for someone in particular?

00:11:14.174 --> 00:11:15.759 position:50% align:center
Yes. Shinomiya.

00:11:15.842 --> 00:11:18.553 position:50% align:center
Okay!

00:11:18.636 --> 00:11:20.638 position:50% align:center
Hey, hey!

00:11:20.722 --> 00:11:22.057 position:50% align:center
Shinomiya!

00:11:22.140 --> 00:11:24.601 position:50% align:center
Guess what? Prez came
here to talk to you!

00:11:24.684 --> 00:11:25.685 position:50% align:center
Th-The President?

00:11:25.769 --> 00:11:26.978 position:50% align:center
[STUDENT 4B]
Well, this is a first...

00:11:27.062 --> 00:11:28.480 position:50% align:center
[STUDENT 4C] ...they
would make a cute couple.

00:11:28.563 --> 00:11:31.566 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA squeals]

00:11:32.609 --> 00:11:35.362 position:50% align:center
So, uh, what did
you wanna talk about?

00:11:35.445 --> 00:11:38.865 position:50% align:center
It's kinda private,
but also important.

00:11:38.948 --> 00:11:40.158 position:50% align:center
I've decided I need you...

00:11:40.241 --> 00:11:41.785 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA, STUDENTS gasping]

00:11:41.868 --> 00:11:43.953 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI]
...to help plan a strategy.

00:11:44.037 --> 00:11:45.580 position:50% align:center
You know, for the election.

00:11:45.663 --> 00:11:47.457 position:50% align:center
Meet me behind the
building after school

00:11:47.540 --> 00:11:50.460 position:50% align:center
and I'll tell you the details.

00:11:50.543 --> 00:11:52.295 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA squeals]

00:11:52.379 --> 00:11:54.005 position:50% align:center
It's about time, right?

00:11:54.089 --> 00:11:55.173 position:50% align:center
[MAKI]
This is old news.

00:11:55.256 --> 00:11:56.633 position:50% align:center
They're always
together after school,

00:11:56.716 --> 00:11:58.468 position:50% align:center
so why wouldn't they be dating?

00:11:58.551 --> 00:11:59.844 position:50% align:center
[KASHIWAGI giggles]

00:11:59.928 --> 00:12:01.388 position:50% align:center
[STUDENTS squealing]

00:12:01.471 --> 00:12:03.264 position:50% align:center
You used to drop by
the student council office

00:12:03.348 --> 00:12:04.224 position:50% align:center
every once in while!

00:12:04.307 --> 00:12:05.308 position:50% align:center
So what's the scoop?

00:12:05.392 --> 00:12:07.227 position:50% align:center
Spill it!

00:12:07.310 --> 00:12:09.354 position:50% align:center
I don't think they're
together, but...

00:12:09.437 --> 00:12:10.689 position:50% align:center
...that could change.

00:12:10.772 --> 00:12:13.191 position:50% align:center
[NARRATOR]
Ooh. This is getting juicy!

00:12:13.274 --> 00:12:15.360 position:50% align:center
[STUDENT C]
Everything's fine, don't panic!

00:12:15.443 --> 00:12:16.444 position:50% align:center
Absolutely!

00:12:16.528 --> 00:12:17.904 position:50% align:center
[NARRATOR]
A topic as hot as wildfire

00:12:17.987 --> 00:12:19.739 position:50% align:center
is naturally going
to spread like it,

00:12:19.823 --> 00:12:22.742 position:50% align:center
especially with the
help of social media.

00:12:22.826 --> 00:12:24.786 position:50% align:center
How's the situation
on the ground?

00:12:24.869 --> 00:12:27.956 position:50% align:center
Well, so far, nothing
to make note of.

00:12:28.039 --> 00:12:30.375 position:50% align:center
We're keeping our distance
so as not to interfere.

00:12:30.458 --> 00:12:31.292 position:50% align:center
It's here!

00:12:31.376 --> 00:12:32.460 position:50% align:center
Your moment!

00:12:32.544 --> 00:12:33.878 position:50% align:center
Wh-What moment?

00:12:33.962 --> 00:12:35.964 position:50% align:center
Good luck. I'm rooting for you!

00:12:36.047 --> 00:12:38.383 position:50% align:center
I have no idea what
you're talking about.

00:12:38.466 --> 00:12:40.593 position:50% align:center
Don't worry,
all systems are go!

00:12:40.677 --> 00:12:42.303 position:50% align:center
What are you talking about?

00:12:42.387 --> 00:12:44.472 position:50% align:center
Yo, Prez! Mad props!

00:12:44.556 --> 00:12:46.474 position:50% align:center
You guys aren't
making any sense.

00:12:46.558 --> 00:12:48.560 position:50% align:center
[NARRATOR]
The result!

00:12:54.315 --> 00:12:55.734 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI]
Wait a second.

00:12:55.817 --> 00:12:57.610 position:50% align:center
What on earth is happening?!

00:12:57.694 --> 00:12:58.486 position:50% align:center
Go on!

00:12:58.570 --> 00:13:00.071 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI]
This feels like

00:13:00.155 --> 00:13:02.866 position:50% align:center
the kind of setup where a guy
confesses his love to his crush!

00:13:02.949 --> 00:13:04.409 position:50% align:center
[CHIKA]
Go.

00:13:04.492 --> 00:13:07.120 position:50% align:center
Ask Kaguya to be in charge of
your speeches like you want.

00:13:07.203 --> 00:13:09.080 position:50% align:center
Get it over and
done with already!

00:13:09.164 --> 00:13:12.584 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI] Leave it to Fujiwara
to be completely oblivious!

00:13:12.667 --> 00:13:13.835 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA whimpers]

00:13:13.918 --> 00:13:15.253 position:50% align:center
[gulps]

00:13:16.463 --> 00:13:19.382 position:50% align:center
You, um, had something to say?

00:13:19.466 --> 00:13:21.384 position:50% align:center
Yeah... so about that...

00:13:21.468 --> 00:13:24.054 position:50% align:center
[NARRATOR] Countless eyes
were locked on to them.

00:13:24.137 --> 00:13:27.015 position:50% align:center
The air behind the school
was permeated with expectation

00:13:27.098 --> 00:13:30.185 position:50% align:center
of a manly confession
of love from Shirogane!

00:13:30.268 --> 00:13:31.603 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI]
There'll be hell to pay

00:13:31.686 --> 00:13:35.148 position:50% align:center
if I don't ask the question
they're expecting me to!

00:13:35.231 --> 00:13:38.401 position:50% align:center
I was wondering if you'd agree
to be in charge of my speeches.

00:13:38.485 --> 00:13:39.819 position:50% align:center
[STUDENTS yelling]
Seriously?!

00:13:39.903 --> 00:13:44.908 position:50% align:center
[STUDENTS shouting]

00:13:46.993 --> 00:13:47.744 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA]
Aw...

00:13:47.827 --> 00:13:52.123 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI screaming]

00:13:53.375 --> 00:13:57.212 position:50% align:center
Oh, hey. It seems we've
got ourselves an audience.

00:13:57.295 --> 00:13:59.255 position:50% align:center
Yes, I noticed.

00:13:59.339 --> 00:14:01.966 position:50% align:center
But... it's okay with me.

00:14:02.050 --> 00:14:04.594 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI] I think you
might have the wrong idea.

00:14:04.678 --> 00:14:06.096 position:50% align:center
Jeez!

00:14:06.179 --> 00:14:08.890 position:50% align:center
What's embarrassing about
asking your former VP for help?

00:14:08.973 --> 00:14:10.141 position:50% align:center
Right, so, um,
the thing is that I--

00:14:10.225 --> 00:14:11.351 position:50% align:center
[CHIKA]
Remember!

00:14:11.434 --> 00:14:13.895 position:50% align:center
You chose Kaguya when
you could've had me!

00:14:13.978 --> 00:14:16.106 position:50% align:center
So pull yourself together and
ask!

00:14:16.189 --> 00:14:19.401 position:50% align:center
[STUDENTS gasping, chattering]

00:14:19.484 --> 00:14:20.860 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI]
Don't make the situation worse

00:14:20.944 --> 00:14:22.404 position:50% align:center
than it already is!

00:14:22.487 --> 00:14:23.947 position:50% align:center
[STUDENT 4D]
Are you gonna do it or not?!

00:14:24.030 --> 00:14:26.658 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI growls]
I lose no matter what!

00:14:26.741 --> 00:14:29.077 position:50% align:center
[STUDENTS clamoring]

00:14:29.160 --> 00:14:29.911 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI]
Um.

00:14:29.994 --> 00:14:31.329 position:50% align:center
Hey...

00:14:33.998 --> 00:14:36.251 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI]
...Shinomiya.

00:14:36.334 --> 00:14:39.379 position:50% align:center
Ah, yes?

00:14:39.462 --> 00:14:40.380 position:50% align:center
Uh?

00:14:40.463 --> 00:14:44.676 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI grunts]

00:14:44.759 --> 00:14:48.722 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI]
Maybe... it's better this way.

00:14:48.805 --> 00:14:50.598 position:50% align:center
I wanted to make
Kaguya Shinomiya

00:14:50.682 --> 00:14:53.852 position:50% align:center
confess her undying love to me.

00:14:53.935 --> 00:14:56.646 position:50% align:center
It wasn't just
a matter of pride.

00:14:56.730 --> 00:14:59.524 position:50% align:center
No, it went deeper than that.

00:14:59.607 --> 00:15:01.109 position:50% align:center
We come from
different backgrounds,

00:15:01.192 --> 00:15:03.653 position:50% align:center
so I thought her confession
would be necessary

00:15:03.737 --> 00:15:05.780 position:50% align:center
before we could date as equals.

00:15:06.906 --> 00:15:08.408 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI] But I feel
too strongly about her

00:15:08.491 --> 00:15:11.286 position:50% align:center
to keep making excuses.

00:15:11.369 --> 00:15:13.204 position:50% align:center
Perhaps it's time.

00:15:13.288 --> 00:15:16.124 position:50% align:center
Hey, listen.

00:15:16.207 --> 00:15:18.084 position:50% align:center
Shinomiya!

00:15:23.548 --> 00:15:26.509 position:50% align:center
Would you mind being in charge
of my campaign speeches?

00:15:26.593 --> 00:15:28.511 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA groans]

00:15:33.308 --> 00:15:37.145 position:50% align:center
Oh, boy. You are hopeless.

00:15:37.228 --> 00:15:39.189 position:50% align:center
Now it's your turn to listen.

00:15:39.272 --> 00:15:41.066 position:50% align:center
Whether it's about
speeches or anything else,

00:15:41.149 --> 00:15:43.109 position:50% align:center
I have one thing to say.

00:15:43.193 --> 00:15:45.403 position:50% align:center
And it's the same response...

00:15:45.487 --> 00:15:47.447 position:50% align:center
...for all of your questions.

00:15:51.451 --> 00:15:53.661 position:50% align:center
Yes. It's my pleasure.

00:15:53.745 --> 00:15:54.496 position:50% align:center
[STUDENT 4F]
What'd she say?

00:15:54.579 --> 00:15:57.499 position:50% align:center
[STUDENTS chattering]

00:15:57.582 --> 00:15:59.125 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI gasps]

00:16:01.169 --> 00:16:04.172 position:50% align:center
Come on. Let's go
before they start to riot.

00:16:04.255 --> 00:16:06.424 position:50% align:center
Uh, right.

00:16:06.508 --> 00:16:08.385 position:50% align:center
[NARRATOR]
Results for today's battle:

00:16:08.468 --> 00:16:09.844 position:50% align:center
It's a tie.

00:16:09.928 --> 00:16:11.429 position:50% align:center
Wait, you guys!

00:16:11.513 --> 00:16:12.722 position:50% align:center
[STUDENTS yelling]

00:16:12.806 --> 00:16:13.932 position:50% align:center
[NARRATOR] It's the
start of the election arc

00:16:14.015 --> 00:16:15.892 position:50% align:center
everyone's been waiting for!

00:16:15.975 --> 00:16:19.437 position:50% align:center
Or it will be, after the break.

00:16:23.066 --> 00:16:24.567 position:50% align:center
[YU]
Whoa.

00:16:24.651 --> 00:16:26.611 position:50% align:center
You're the
frontrunner, President.

00:16:26.695 --> 00:16:27.779 position:50% align:center
[CHIKA]
Yay!

00:16:27.862 --> 00:16:29.864 position:50% align:center
It's practically in the bag now!

00:16:29.948 --> 00:16:31.116 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI]
Some people voted for me

00:16:31.199 --> 00:16:32.701 position:50% align:center
because they remembered my name,

00:16:32.784 --> 00:16:34.828 position:50% align:center
not what I did for the school.

00:16:34.911 --> 00:16:36.287 position:50% align:center
These numbers can easily change

00:16:36.371 --> 00:16:38.623 position:50% align:center
depending on what
the other candidates do.

00:16:38.707 --> 00:16:40.250 position:50% align:center
--[YU grunts]
--[CHIKA] Mm-hm.

00:16:41.418 --> 00:16:44.087 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI] Who am I kidding?
I've got this on lock!

00:16:44.170 --> 00:16:47.549 position:50% align:center
It's scary how popular I am!
Why even bother campaigning?

00:16:47.632 --> 00:16:50.260 position:50% align:center
I could do nothing and
still win by a landslide!

00:16:50.343 --> 00:16:53.722 position:50% align:center
[CHIKA] Looks like a first-year
girl is in second place.

00:16:53.805 --> 00:16:55.849 position:50% align:center
Do you know who
she is, Ishigami?

00:16:55.932 --> 00:16:57.392 position:50% align:center
[YU]
You honestly think I memorize

00:16:57.475 --> 00:16:59.477 position:50% align:center
the names of my classmates?

00:17:00.562 --> 00:17:02.397 position:50% align:center
Miko Iino, huh?

00:17:02.480 --> 00:17:03.606 position:50% align:center
Miko.

00:17:03.690 --> 00:17:05.233 position:50% align:center
--[CHIKA gasps]
--[YU] Okay.

00:17:05.316 --> 00:17:07.819 position:50% align:center
Turns out I do know that name.

00:17:07.902 --> 00:17:09.279 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI]
Is she well known?

00:17:09.362 --> 00:17:12.157 position:50% align:center
Well... first-years
know who she is.

00:17:12.240 --> 00:17:14.492 position:50% align:center
Academically, she's at
the top of her class.

00:17:14.576 --> 00:17:16.870 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI]
Uh, oh.

00:17:16.953 --> 00:17:20.373 position:50% align:center
Also... she's
a very intense girl.

00:17:20.457 --> 00:17:21.791 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
Please, take one!

00:17:21.875 --> 00:17:25.295 position:50% align:center
[YU] There she is now--
the one handing out the fliers.

00:17:25.378 --> 00:17:28.173 position:50% align:center
Might be better
to show than tell.

00:17:28.256 --> 00:17:31.760 position:50% align:center
You'll know what I mean when you
see her in action for yourself.

00:17:31.843 --> 00:17:33.219 position:50% align:center
Sure.

00:17:34.679 --> 00:17:37.015 position:50% align:center
Please take a moment
to look at this...

00:17:37.098 --> 00:17:38.141 position:50% align:center
...i-if you would.

00:17:38.224 --> 00:17:40.602 position:50% align:center
[YU]
Got a sec?

00:17:40.685 --> 00:17:42.228 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
Possibly.

00:17:42.312 --> 00:17:45.774 position:50% align:center
But I'd rather not waste it on a
loser like you, so make it fast.

00:17:45.857 --> 00:17:47.567 position:50% align:center
[YU]
Ouch, that hurt.

00:17:47.650 --> 00:17:50.070 position:50% align:center
I'm not here to waste
your precious time.

00:17:50.153 --> 00:17:52.155 position:50% align:center
Thought you two should meet.

00:17:52.238 --> 00:17:54.574 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI]
So you're Miko Iino?

00:17:57.327 --> 00:17:58.078 position:50% align:center
Yes.

00:17:58.161 --> 00:17:59.662 position:50% align:center
[NARRATOR]
Miko Iino.

00:17:59.746 --> 00:18:02.457 position:50% align:center
A first-year student
at Shuchiin Academy.

00:18:02.540 --> 00:18:05.502 position:50% align:center
She's a talented youth
who, like Shirogane,

00:18:05.585 --> 00:18:07.671 position:50% align:center
is at the top of her class.

00:18:07.754 --> 00:18:09.506 position:50% align:center
Her father is
a High Court Judge,

00:18:09.589 --> 00:18:11.758 position:50% align:center
which makes her Public
Morals Committee membership

00:18:11.841 --> 00:18:13.176 position:50% align:center
all the more fitting.

00:18:13.259 --> 00:18:16.096 position:50% align:center
She's a diligent honors student
with exemplary conduct.

00:18:16.179 --> 00:18:18.056 position:50% align:center
She's also only four foot eight!

00:18:18.139 --> 00:18:19.891 position:50% align:center
Cute, right?

00:18:19.974 --> 00:18:22.560 position:50% align:center
It's nice to meet
you... I guess...

00:18:22.644 --> 00:18:24.437 position:50% align:center
...Former President, sir.

00:18:24.521 --> 00:18:26.981 position:50% align:center
Thanks. And congrats.

00:18:27.065 --> 00:18:28.733 position:50% align:center
Heard you're at
the top of your class.

00:18:28.817 --> 00:18:31.903 position:50% align:center
Yes. I have been
ever since day one.

00:18:31.986 --> 00:18:34.364 position:50% align:center
Oh, cool.

00:18:34.447 --> 00:18:36.783 position:50% align:center
Academics are important,
but they're not everything.

00:18:36.866 --> 00:18:39.828 position:50% align:center
Getting real-world
experience is equally essential!

00:18:39.911 --> 00:18:42.997 position:50% align:center
[CHIKA] Wait. Does he really see
himself as this girl's rival,

00:18:43.081 --> 00:18:45.000 position:50% align:center
or is he just being petty?

00:18:45.083 --> 00:18:46.751 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI]
Handing out fliers, eh?

00:18:46.835 --> 00:18:48.461 position:50% align:center
Dull work,
but it builds character.

00:18:48.545 --> 00:18:51.172 position:50% align:center
[MIKO] It's more than you've
been doing, which is nothing.

00:18:51.256 --> 00:18:53.925 position:50% align:center
Has the king become
complacent in his castle?

00:18:54.009 --> 00:18:57.470 position:50% align:center
Or is he every bit as
careless as he appears to be?

00:18:57.554 --> 00:18:59.681 position:50% align:center
Exposure is the
essence of campaigning,

00:18:59.764 --> 00:19:01.433 position:50% align:center
so, yeah, fliers are good.

00:19:01.516 --> 00:19:04.352 position:50% align:center
But... that kind of
grunt work isn't necessary

00:19:04.436 --> 00:19:06.479 position:50% align:center
when you've got an
actual track record.

00:19:06.563 --> 00:19:07.814 position:50% align:center
[OSARAGI]
I disagree.

00:19:07.897 --> 00:19:09.774 position:50% align:center
There's no excuse for
that kind of carelessness.

00:19:09.858 --> 00:19:12.152 position:50% align:center
You may be fine doing nothing,
but we're inviting students

00:19:12.235 --> 00:19:14.612 position:50% align:center
the chance to ponder
alternative political platforms,

00:19:14.696 --> 00:19:16.448 position:50% align:center
like a wholesome
administration should.

00:19:16.531 --> 00:19:17.282 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI, YU gasp]

00:19:17.365 --> 00:19:18.783 position:50% align:center
To each their own.

00:19:18.867 --> 00:19:21.286 position:50% align:center
We're stepping up to make
Shuchiin Academy an even better,

00:19:21.369 --> 00:19:23.788 position:50% align:center
nobler place than it already is.

00:19:23.872 --> 00:19:25.331 position:50% align:center
Through my campaign,

00:19:25.415 --> 00:19:28.543 position:50% align:center
I'll convey that message to
every student who lends an ear.

00:19:28.626 --> 00:19:32.130 position:50% align:center
Jeez, you keep that silver
tongue well polished, don't you?

00:19:32.213 --> 00:19:34.674 position:50% align:center
It's pink, you dummy.

00:19:34.758 --> 00:19:36.551 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI]
Having ideals is fine,

00:19:36.634 --> 00:19:39.054 position:50% align:center
but you know you can't
attain them, right?

00:19:39.137 --> 00:19:41.306 position:50% align:center
Election day can't come
soon enough!

00:19:41.389 --> 00:19:43.558 position:50% align:center
Reality is gonna whack
you upside your head

00:19:43.641 --> 00:19:45.643 position:50% align:center
like a sledgehammer! [cackles]

00:19:45.727 --> 00:19:50.273 position:50% align:center
Stop it, guys! You sound
like villains in a melodrama!

00:19:50.357 --> 00:19:53.443 position:50% align:center
Ideas without ideals...
What a meaningless concept.

00:19:53.526 --> 00:19:57.364 position:50% align:center
You see? Might wanna rethink
who's spouting nonsense here!

00:19:57.447 --> 00:20:00.075 position:50% align:center
Sorry. Miyuki is
saying that stuff

00:20:00.158 --> 00:20:02.077 position:50% align:center
because you make
him self-conscious.

00:20:02.160 --> 00:20:03.703 position:50% align:center
Greetings, Fujiwara.

00:20:03.787 --> 00:20:06.623 position:50% align:center
Oh! I didn't realize
you knew who I was.

00:20:06.706 --> 00:20:08.208 position:50% align:center
Yes, of course!

00:20:08.291 --> 00:20:10.085 position:50% align:center
Umm, question.

00:20:10.168 --> 00:20:12.712 position:50% align:center
Since we're meeting like this,

00:20:12.796 --> 00:20:15.465 position:50% align:center
once I'm elected as
Student Council president,

00:20:15.548 --> 00:20:18.677 position:50% align:center
would you be my vice president
and run the school by my side?

00:20:18.760 --> 00:20:20.053 position:50% align:center
[shrieks]

00:20:20.136 --> 00:20:23.306 position:50% align:center
[YU, MIYUKI screaming]

00:20:23.390 --> 00:20:25.350 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI] Why would you want
Fujiwara of all people?!

00:20:25.433 --> 00:20:26.434 position:50% align:center
[YU]
If you actually knew her,

00:20:26.518 --> 00:20:28.061 position:50% align:center
you'd never make
such a stupid request!

00:20:28.144 --> 00:20:30.772 position:50% align:center
Okay, now you two are just
being straight up rude!

00:20:30.855 --> 00:20:32.607 position:50% align:center
You seem like a sensible girl!

00:20:32.691 --> 00:20:34.275 position:50% align:center
Can you convince your
friend to change her mind

00:20:34.359 --> 00:20:35.568 position:50% align:center
before mistakes are made?

00:20:35.652 --> 00:20:36.861 position:50% align:center
[OSARAGI]
No.

00:20:36.945 --> 00:20:39.030 position:50% align:center
Fujiwara would make
a suitable vice president

00:20:39.114 --> 00:20:40.657 position:50% align:center
from a logical standpoint.

00:20:40.740 --> 00:20:41.825 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI]
What logic is that?!

00:20:41.908 --> 00:20:43.410 position:50% align:center
You must not know
very much about her

00:20:43.493 --> 00:20:45.912 position:50% align:center
if such rubbish would
ever cross your mind!

00:20:45.995 --> 00:20:48.456 position:50% align:center
I can't think of a
single person who compares!

00:20:48.540 --> 00:20:51.209 position:50% align:center
[CHIKA giggles]

00:20:51.292 --> 00:20:52.919 position:50% align:center
She took home the
grand prize at the

00:20:53.003 --> 00:20:56.506 position:50% align:center
national PTA piano competition!
How amazing is that?

00:20:56.589 --> 00:20:58.341 position:50% align:center
Way back in fourth grade.

00:20:58.425 --> 00:21:00.844 position:50% align:center
She also speaks five
different languages!

00:21:00.927 --> 00:21:02.721 position:50% align:center
Well, my folks are diplomats.

00:21:02.804 --> 00:21:04.264 position:50% align:center
[MIKO] And even though
she's positively brilliant,

00:21:04.347 --> 00:21:05.890 position:50% align:center
she only boasts average grades!

00:21:05.974 --> 00:21:09.144 position:50% align:center
Yes. Average. Yay...

00:21:09.227 --> 00:21:11.479 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
Ever since I was a little kid,

00:21:11.563 --> 00:21:14.816 position:50% align:center
I've played the piano
and idolized Fujiwara!

00:21:14.899 --> 00:21:16.943 position:50% align:center
She's a prodigy who's
light years ahead of me

00:21:17.027 --> 00:21:18.278 position:50% align:center
and every last one of us

00:21:18.361 --> 00:21:21.656 position:50% align:center
is lucky to even be in
her presence! You hear me?!

00:21:22.824 --> 00:21:24.617 position:50% align:center
Go on... Praise me more.

00:21:24.701 --> 00:21:25.994 position:50% align:center
[MIKO] If there's one
thing I know for sure,

00:21:26.077 --> 00:21:27.912 position:50% align:center
it's that Fujiwara
is incredible!

00:21:27.996 --> 00:21:29.664 position:50% align:center
People have been treating
me like a has-been

00:21:29.748 --> 00:21:31.791 position:50% align:center
ever since I stopped
playing, so I'm flattered!

00:21:31.875 --> 00:21:34.502 position:50% align:center
You may be the favorite
as of this moment.

00:21:34.586 --> 00:21:35.754 position:50% align:center
However...

00:21:35.837 --> 00:21:38.423 position:50% align:center
...I refuse to back
down on my ideals!

00:21:38.506 --> 00:21:39.841 position:50% align:center
With time,

00:21:39.924 --> 00:21:43.261 position:50% align:center
people will come to understand
them the same way I do.

00:21:43.345 --> 00:21:45.555 position:50% align:center
If I wasn't sure
before, I am now.

00:21:45.638 --> 00:21:47.474 position:50% align:center
Fujiwara and I are going to win!

00:21:47.557 --> 00:21:50.185 position:50% align:center
Don't take us lightly!

00:21:50.268 --> 00:21:53.396 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI] A few compliments,
and suddenly you're on her side?

00:21:55.273 --> 00:21:57.400 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI]
So that's Miko Iino.

00:21:57.484 --> 00:22:00.695 position:50% align:center
It looks like we'll
have to step up our game.

00:22:00.779 --> 00:22:03.073 position:50% align:center
Personally, I wouldn't
worry too much, Prez.

00:22:03.156 --> 00:22:04.115 position:50% align:center
How come?

00:22:04.199 --> 00:22:06.993 position:50% align:center
Easy. Just read the flier.

00:22:07.077 --> 00:22:09.621 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI]
Hm?

00:22:09.704 --> 00:22:12.207 position:50% align:center
[YU] Shaved heads, no cell
phones, and weekly bag checks?

00:22:12.290 --> 00:22:15.377 position:50% align:center
Her strict policy is
more a flaw than an asset.

00:22:15.460 --> 00:22:18.421 position:50% align:center
Those fliers aren't doing
her any favors, that's for sure.

00:22:18.505 --> 00:22:19.756 position:50% align:center
But she doesn't see it.

00:22:19.839 --> 00:22:22.467 position:50% align:center
Yeah... right.

00:22:22.550 --> 00:22:26.054 position:50% align:center
[NARRATOR] Shirogane dominates
the election even more.

00:22:26.137 --> 00:22:27.263 position:50% align:center
[YU]
I wish it would sit her down

00:22:27.347 --> 00:22:28.765 position:50% align:center
and tell her how crazy she acts.

00:22:28.848 --> 00:22:32.310 position:50% align:center
Maybe then she'd realize
what kind of person she is.

00:22:32.394 --> 00:22:35.522 position:50% align:center
[NARRATOR]
As for Kaguya...

00:22:35.605 --> 00:22:38.191 position:50% align:center
Where did everybody go?

00:22:38.274 --> 00:22:41.820 position:50% align:center
[CHIKA chuckles, grunts]